[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    140[0m:[38;5;10m[49m #### N1 - MEDIUM: VPC Endpoint for SageMaker Runtime Not Explicitly Called Out
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    141[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    142[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Location:** Prerequisites table, "VPC" row
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    143[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    144[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Issue:** The prerequisites mention "SageMaker endpoints, Glue jobs, and Lambda functions in VPC with VPC endpoints for S3, DynamoDB, SageMaker Runtime, and CloudWatch Logs." This is correct but could be more explicit. The SageMaker Runtime VPC endpoint (`com.amazonaws.{region}.sagemaker.runtime`) is distinct from the SageMaker API endpoint (`com.amazonaws.{region}.sagemaker.api`). The scoring Lambda needs the runtime endpoint to invoke the model. The training pipeline needs the API endpoint to create training jobs. These are different VPC endpoints with different security group configurations.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    145[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    146[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Suggested fix:** Expand the VPC row to list specific endpoint service names:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    147[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    148[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    149[0m:[38;5;10m[49m VPC Endpoints Required:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    150[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - com.amazonaws.{region}.s3 (Gateway)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    151[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - com.amazonaws.{region}.dynamodb (Gateway)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    152[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - com.amazonaws.{region}.sagemaker.runtime (Interface, for model invocation)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    153[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - com.amazonaws.{region}.healthlake (Interface, for FHIR queries)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    154[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - com.amazonaws.{region}.states (Interface, for Step Functions)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    155[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - com.amazonaws.{region}.logs (Interface, for CloudWatch Logs)
