[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    187[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    188[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Issue:** The "Why These Services" paragraphs follow a pattern of "**Service Name for X.**" followed by explanation. This is structurally fine and matches the recipe guide. However, the HealthLake paragraph includes "HealthLake provides a FHIR-native data store that can ingest clinical data from EHR systems and normalize it into a queryable format." This reads slightly more like product documentation than the engineer-explaining-over-lunch voice used elsewhere. Compare with the SageMaker paragraph which says "Readmission scoring needs to happen within hours of discharge, which means you need a model endpoint..." (problem-first framing).
