[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The two HIGH findings (S1: IAM scoping, S2: DynamoDB access control) are both security concerns that don't conflict with each other or with other expert recommendations. They can be addressed independently. S1 is a straightforward fix (add resource ARNs to the prerequisites table). S2 requires a brief architectural discussion paragraph but doesn't change the core design.
