[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    258[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### What's Done Well
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    259[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Clinical accuracy is excellent.** The CMS HRRP description, penalty calculation methodology, condition coverage, and planned vs. unplanned readmission distinction are all correct and well-explained.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **The Technology section is outstanding.** The discussion of base rate problems, information availability constraints, social determinant gaps, calibration requirements, and fairness considerations demonstrates genuine domain expertise. A reader who has never built a readmission model would understand the problem space thoroughly after reading this section.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Feature categories are comprehensive and clinically appropriate.** The grouping into index admission, clinical severity, prior utilization, medication complexity, functional/social, and discharge process indicators covers the standard feature domains used in published readmission models.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Performance benchmarks are realistic.** The C-statistic range of 0.68-0.75 is consistent with published literature. The recipe doesn't overclaim model performance, which builds trust.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **The Honest Take is the recipe's strongest section.** "The model is the easy part" and "the intervention matters more than the prediction" are insights that only come from operational experience. This section alone justifies the recipe's existence.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Calibration discussion is rare and valuable.** Most readmission prediction tutorials skip calibration entirely. This recipe correctly identifies it as "the most underrated requirement" and explains why it matters for operational decision-making.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **The fairness section is thoughtful.** Acknowledging that the same model can serve helpful or harmful purposes depending on operationalization is a mature perspective that most technical cookbooks avoid.
